parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Brake Lines and ABS System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of brake lines and ABS system failure can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle takes an extremely long time to stop
ABS light comes on
and the vehicle pulls to one side during braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ABS system malfunction can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: ABS light comes on
brakes engage at low speeds

and the vehicle pulls to one side during braking.
